Adobe Creative SuiteHaley Carruthers
Urban Planner at Kimley-Horn
United States
Summary
My knowledge of planning brings diverse perspective to cultivate
comprehensive solutions centered in community engagement,
analysis and story. I have worked on small area plans, long-range
comprehensive planning, parks, recreation and open space planning,
active transportation planning and equity planning. I am also skilled
in building an inclusive space for community members to provide
input and share vital feedback for the planning process. I have
experience leading community discussions for concept visioning,
identifying prioritization and Diversity, equity and inclusion topics.
I am proficient in ArcGIS tools that leverage viable solutions for
communities centered in data analysis. These tools include ArcGIS
PRO, Business Analyst and ArcGIS Online. Using these resources
I have built equity index’s, developed walk and drive time network
maps and conducted resource based analysis. I am a strong graphic
designer with skills in adobe creative cloud that help create a strong
project identity that encourages community response and buy in.

Civic Leadership Fellow

Dallas, Texas, United States
  Page 1 of 3    
My role as a civil leadership fellow is to learn how to strategically lead
community outreach projects. Weekly I assist in grassroots initiatives led
by my field and advocacy managers. I help facilitate meetings by leading
brainstorming sessions to help foster innovative solutions. I help my education
director build curriculum for future fellows and volunteers for efficient and
holistic onboarding. I lead projects and manage events by developing assets
and reports. This fellowship allows me to develop essential communication
skills for both outreach within our community and investors. My opportunity
with MOVE has allowed me to receive hands-on skills in public policy and
effective communication techniques to bridge the gap between community
members and government entities.
Walt Disney Imagineering
Master Planning Intern
June 2019 - August 2020  (1 year 3 months)
Glendale
The master planning studio I worked for had 4 departments: design, pre-
development, planning and strategy. My role as an intern was to assist within
each department on a diverse set of projects. For the pre-development team
I researched city ordinances in respective cities to inform project parameters.
I would often participate in site inspections and document key findings. From
here I would collaborate with the planning and strategy team by mapping data
in GIS to inform planning techniques. My research was self-facilitated, so I
learned time management and how to deliver clear concise findings to my
supervisors. This research and analysis informed parts of our annual plan
for the Disneyland Resort and Shanghai Resort. To assist the design team
I produced maps, project concepts, decks, or presentations for leadership.
These deliverables often were to bridge the gap of communication between
our Master Planning team to other parts of WDI. My time as a master planning
intern taught me multi-disciplinary collaboration, attention to detail and skills to
communicate through different mediums.
NoHo Business Improvement District
Intern
May 2018 - August 2018  (4 months)
Greater New York City Area
I ran data research for the BID, maintained its database for future usage,
interfaced with the local businesses, and collaborated with the other 73 BIDs
throughout the city. The maintenance of data was crucial in documenting the
history of the community and its buildings. Mainly working in excel, I populated
  Page 2 of 3    
and organized the data for future uses. I engaged with the community and
learned to be receptive to the concerns of the people. This enabled me to help
guide the BID’s initiatives. Working directly with the community has taught me
the importance of being attentive to user needs, communication, and patience.
